modules.description: This module converts JSON values into OCaml values, providing functions to extract specific types like strings, booleans, integers, floats, and more complex structures like lists, arrays, and result types. It works directly with `Yojson.Basic.t` values, allowing safe and precise decoding of JSON data. Concrete use cases include parsing JSON API responses into typed OCaml data structures or validating JSON configuration files.

This module converts between JSON values and OCaml primitives, handling types like strings, booleans, numbers, and collections. It supports parsing JSON into typed OCaml values and serializing OCaml values into JSON structures. Use it to decode JSON inputs into specific types or encode OCaml data for JSON output, such as processing API responses or serializing configuration data.

This module constructs JSON values from OCaml primitives and structured types. It supports conversions for strings, booleans, integers, floats, lists, arrays, options, and results, producing extensible JSON-like variant types. Use it to serialize OCaml data into JSON representations for APIs, configuration files, or data interchange formats.
